							<div class="modal-body py-0">
								  
								<p>The Integrated Monitoring, Reporting and Verification (MRV) system and database (or iMRV Tool) for South Sudan's Nationally Determined Contribution (NDC) has been developed to effectively and efficiently  implement the Paris Agreement and Enhance Transparency Framework (ETF) requirements. 
								The iMRV Tool transparently communicate the South Sudan's climate actions (mitigation and adaptation), strategies, programmes, climate finance and SDG impacts, to the domestic and international stakeholders, development partners and international community.</p> 
								<p>The South Sudan's iMRV Tool provides an overarching structure, approach, and methodology towards:</p> 
								<p><b>National GHG Inventory</b>: 
								The National GHG inventory is typically an annual inventory of anthropogenic emissions by sources and removals by sinks of greenhouse gases (GHGs) not controlled by the Montreal Protocol. Direct GHG emissions of gases: Carbon dioxide (CO2), Methane (CH4), Nitrous oxide (N2O), Oxides of nitrogen (NOx), Carbon monoxide (CO), Non-methane volatile organic compounds (NMVOC)and Sulphur dioxide (SO2) from different sectors like: Energy, Industrial Processes and Product use (IPPU), Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use (AFOLU) and Waste.  
								The iMRV Tool also includes implied emission factors, activity data, and supplementary information.</p>
								<p><b>Mitigation Action Tracking</b>: The Mitigation Action Tracking Module focus on both project implementation and operation phase. The bottom-up approach has been applied for a comprehensive and integrated system considering the unique requirement of South Sudan. This module has living framework and will be updated on a periodic basis to integrate the existing national processes for project monitoring, avoid duplication and maximize the use of resources. 
								The module allows for efficient integration and strengthening between what exists and expected processes , importantly, appropriate monitoring indicators and parameters (e.g., raw data needs) both at the project and programme level.</p> 
								<p><b>Adaptation Action and Priorities Tracking</b>: The Adaptation Action Module includes monitoring and tracking of adaptation actions and priories of South Sudan, the module has been designed as per the UNDP CAIT Tool. This module follow bottom approach and methodology for tracking qualitative and quantitative impacts on Disaster (Drought and Flood) Risk Management, Food and Nutrition Security, Water and the Blue Economy, Forestry, Wildlife and Tourism, Health, Sanitation and Human Settlement, Manufacturing, Energy and Transport along with impact on Gender and other Vulnerable population; with periodicity of monitoring.</p>    
								<p><b>Climate Finance</b>: The South Sudan has given due importance to international and domestic financial flow for Climate Change (mitigation and adaptation), also defined under the Paris Agreement and ETF. The aspect of climate finance module includes tracking, monitoring and reporting of the international finance received, disbursement of the international and domestic financial flow towards the implementation of NDC commitment and achieving climate change objectives (mitigation and adaptation) along with interlinkages to sustainable development goals (SDGs).</p> 
								<p><b>Co-benefits (SDGs and Gender Impact)</b>: The SDG Module of iMRV Tool includes monitoring and progress tracking of SDG impact of climate actions. The SDG module is based on the UNDP's Climate Action Impact (CAIT) methodology and customized for specific requirements of South Sudan. The SDG module uses a bottom-up approach to track 'significant, direct impacts on all 17 SDGs'.</p> 
								<p>The South Sudan's iMRV Tool applies a flexible approach and bottom-up methodologies, based on the current international best practices and specific circumstances and requirements of the country. The iMRV Tool has been developed in support of UNDP and will be strengthen over time with enhance capabilities and capacities of stakeholders, international guidance and requirements.</p> 
								
								<p><b>iMRV Tool Benefits</b>:</p>
								<p>-	Informed decision making for national and international policymakers</p> 
								<p>-	Provide the information basis for planning and implementing climate actions</p> 
								<p>-	Unlock new sources of finance to combat climate change by documenting impact and good governance practices</p> 
								<p>-	Identify needs for technical and financial support and assist in institutionalising activities related to reporting on climate change</p>  
								<p>-	Build national capacities and ensure sustainability of reporting processes</p>
								<p>-	Strengthen and enhance South Sudan's efforts towered climate change mitigation and adaptation; and achieving global climate change objectives and targets.</p>
